The 1963 Wimbledon Championships took place on the outdoor grass courts at the All England Lawn Tennis and Croquet Club in Wimbledon, London, United Kingdom. The tournament ran from 24 June until 5 July. It was the 77th staging of the Wimbledon Championships, and the third Grand Slam tennis event of 1963. United States Chuck McKinley defeated Australia Fred Stolle 9-7, 6-1, 6-4  Australia Margaret Court defeated United States Billie Jean King 6-3, 6-4  Mexico Rafael Osuna / Mexico Antonio Palafox defeated France Claude Barclay / France Pierre Darmon, 4-6, 6-2, 6-2, 6-2  Brazil Maria Bueno / United States Darlene Hard defeated Australia Robyn Ebbern / Australia Margaret Smith, 8-6, 9-7  Australia Margaret Smith / Australia Ken Fletcher defeated United States Darlene Hard / South Africa Bob Hewitt, 11-9, 6-4  
